main event: On June 25, 1955, near Duncan, Oklahoma, a round, light green object with an orange trail, appearing fuzzy and cutting off square at the trailing edge, was observed for 5 seconds and concluded to be a meteor sighting.
interesting points: The object was described as round, light green with an orange trail, and the outline or object appeared fuzzy.
The sighting lasted only 5 seconds, and the object was concluded to be a meteor sighting.
The report mentions the witness being a military source from the 11th Bombardment Wing and that there was no intercept action taken.
The weather conditions at the time of the sighting included a wind speed of 125 knots and a visibility of 12,000 feet.

There was no physical evidence of the sighting, and the document contains a note stating that its transmission or revelation of its contents in any manner to an unauthorized person is prohibited by law.
sighted object: round, light green object with orange trail
